(Reuters) - Amazon.com Inc has started to use thermal cameras at its warehouses to speed up screening for feverish workers who could be infected with the coronavirus, employees told Reuters.
Other companies that have explored using the thermal camera technology include Tyson Foods Inc and Intel Corp.
FILE PHOTO: Thermal cameras are pictured in Beaumont, Texas, U.S., April 11, 2020.
Amazon is deploying the technology to screen workers for fevers during the coronavirus pandemic.
Infrared Cameras Inc/Handout via REUTERSThe thermal camera system is faster, two other workers said, with no stopping in front of a screen necessary.